<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
    lang="en"
    metal:use-macro="context/@@malone_template/master"
    i18n:domain="malone">
<body>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
    <form method="POST" action="." style="float: right;">
        <b>Assigned to:</b><br />
        <div tal:replace="structure view/userSelector" /><br />
        <b>Minimum Severity:</b><br />
        <div tal:replace="structure view/severitySelector" /><br />
        <input type="submit" value="Update">
    </form>
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">


    <h1>Bugs Assigned to <span tal:content="context/user/browsername">
    Person</span></h1>
    
    <div tal:condition="context/assignedBugs">
    
        <table class="listing rowNavigation" width="100%">

            <tr>
                <th>Bug #</th>
                <th>Details</th>
            </tr>

            <tr tal:repeat="bug context/assignedBugs"
                tal:attributes="onclick
                string:window.location='/malone/bugs/${bug/id}'">
                <td><span tal:replace="bug/id">$Bug.id</span>
                    <span tal:condition="bug/name">(<span
                    tal:replace="bug/name">name</span>)</span></td>
                <td tal:attributes="title bug/shortdesc">
                    <b><span tal:replace="bug/title">$Bug.title</span></b></td>
            </tr>
 
        </table>
        
    <p>These are the bugs that are in the work list for <span
    tal:replace="context/user/browsername">the person</span>. These bugs
    might occur in upstream products or distribution packages which <span
    tal:replace="context/user/browsername">the person</span> maintains, or
    they might have been explicitly assigned. Click on the bug to see more
    detail.</p>
        
    </div>

    <div tal:condition="not:context/assignedBugs">
    No bugs are currently assigned to <span
    tal:replace="context/user/browsername">Person</span>. You can assign a bug by
    clicking on the "Add Product" or "Add Package" links near the top of the
    main bug page, assigning the bug to an upstream product or package and then also
    assigning it to a specific person for action.
    </div>
  

</div>

</body>

</html>

